The paper deals with the analysis of fast matrix multiplication algorithms, which is a topic that falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also presents an algorithmic approach to decide the equivalence of polyadic decompositions, which involves computational geometry (cs.CG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The study of equivalence classes of decompositions also involves the use of combinatorial techniques (cs.CC) and linear algebra (cs.SC).
